<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1977,2037]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1977,2002]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[776,851,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">bathos</emphasis>
for “depth” and the 
<typeStatus box="[1079,1127,1978,2002]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1297,1978,2002]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1297,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in reference to the much deeper depth inhabited by the 
<typeStatus box="[628,676,2013,2037]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species relative to the other 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1086,2012,2036]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[997,1086,2012,2036]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
